Spielt antimuslimischer Rassismus eine Rolle für dich? 

Antimuslimischer Rassismus wird zu selten dokumentiert sagt Rima Hanano, Leiterin von CLAIM (@claim_allianz): “Leider ist es halt immer noch so, wer nicht gezählt wird, zählt nicht und ohne Zahlen gibt es auch kein Problem.” 

Teilweise würden Betroffene die Fälle aus Misstrauen gegenüber Behörden nicht anzeigen. Diese Hürde soll über die Seite “I Report” erleichtert werden. Die Initiator:innen wollen Betroffene von antimuslimischem Rassismus unterstützen, indem sie sie an Beratungsstellen vermitteln und ihre Fälle erfassen. 

Die Seite ist ein Projekt von “CLAIM” einer Allianz gegen Islam- und Muslimfeindlichkeit, die vom Bundesministerium für Familie, Senioren, Frauen und Jugend gefördert wird. 

#cosmo #antimuslimischerrassismus #amr #beratung #claim

Non è un’Aston Martin qualunque.
La Vulcan AMR Pro è la versione più estrema mai realizzata della già rarissima Vulcan.
Un’arma da pista costruita in appena 24 esemplari, riservata ai clienti più esclusivi del marchio.

Realizzata dal reparto Q di Aston Martin, la AMR Pro riceve un enorme pacchetto aerodinamico: nuovi dive-plane, passaruota alettati e un gigantesco alettone biplano che genera carico aerodinamico ad alta velocità.

A questo si aggiungono rapporti accorciati, nuove componenti in carbonio alleggerite e una dinamica rivista per massimizzare il bilanciamento in curva.
Il risultato? Una delle auto più feroci e radicali mai create dal brand britannico.
Una vera hypercar da pista, senza compromessi.

Ontem foi o dia de Iemanjá, 02/02. 🧜‍♀️

Rainha das águas, mãe que acolhe, que leva e traz, que ensina com o movimento do mar. Onda vai, onda vem. E a gente, nesse vai e vem da vida, às vezes tenta remar contra a correnteza, resistir ao que é maior que nós. 🌊

Mas aprendi com o mar que onda grande se atravessa mergulhando. No meio do turbilhão, não adianta brigar com a força das águas. Quanto mais lutamos, mais nos cansamos. O segredo é se entregar ao mergulho, confiar na respiração, na pausa, no momento de se recolher antes de emergir. 😮‍💨

Assim é dentro da gente. Em dias de mar revolto, não é a pressa que nos salva, nem o desespero. É o silêncio interno, a coragem de olhar para dentro, de sentir o que precisa ser sentido sem fugir.

Mergulhar é permitir-se atravessar, sem medo do fundo, sem medo do tempo que leva até a superfície. Porque, no fim, toda onda passa. Mas quem aprendeu a mergulhar, nunca mais teme a tempestade.✨

📹 priscillasimoesofc

مقاومت آنتی‌بیوتیکی (AMR) یکی از بزرگ‌ترین تهدیدهای بهداشت عمومی در قرن ۲۱ است که سازمان جهانی بهداشت (WHO) آن را به‌عنوان یک بحران جهانی در حال رشد شناسایی کرده است.

مقاومت آنتی‌بیوتیکی باعث می‌شود عفونت‌ها سخت‌تر یا غیرقابل درمان شوند و خطر گسترش بیماری، بیماری شدید و مرگ افزایش یابد. 

استفاده بیش‌ازحد و نادرست از آنتی‌بیوتیک‌ها  از عوامل اصلی مقاومت آنتی‌بیوتیکی هستند.

راهکارهای جلوگیری از مقاومت آنتی‌بیوتیکی

✅ در سطح افراد جامعه:
 1. مصرف آنتی‌بیوتیک فقط با تجویز پزشک
– هرگز خودسرانه آنتی‌بیوتیک مصرف نکنید.
– برای سرماخوردگی یا ویروس‌هایی مانند آنفلوآنزا، از آنتی‌بیوتیک استفاده نکنید.
 2. تکمیل دوره درمانی
– حتی اگر علائم بهبود یافت، مصرف دارو را طبق دستور پزشک کامل کنید.
 3. عدم استفاده از باقی‌مانده آنتی‌بیوتیک دیگران یا داروی قبلی خودتان

✅ در سطح پزشکان و نظام سلامت:
 1. تجویز منطقی و بر پایه شواهد
– استفاده از راهنماهای کشوری یا جهانی (مثل WHO، NICE) برای تجویز آنتی‌بیوتیک.
– انجام کشت و آنتی‌بیوگرام در صورت لزوم.
 2. پایش و گزارش مقاومت دارویی (Antibiotic Surveillance)
– ثبت و گزارش مقاومت‌ها برای تصمیم‌گیری سیاست‌گذارانه.
 3. آموزش بیماران درباره خطرات مصرف نادرست آنتی‌بیوتیک
 4. استفاده از طبقه‌بندی AWaRe
– دسته‌بندی داروها به “Access”, “Watch”, “Reserve” برای اولویت‌بندی ایمن‌تر.

“I have lived with a congenital kidney condition since birth. While managing kidney disease has been challenging, dealing with infections has been an even greater concern—especially when antibiotics are not effective. 

As a teenager, I underwent major surgery to prevent kidney failure. Since then, I have experienced frequent infections, requiring hospital stays and additional treatments. Some infections have been difficult to treat, delaying my recovery and limiting treatment options. 

Now, as I prepare for the removal of both kidneys, preventing infections is more important than ever. Sepsis is a serious risk, and each infection requires careful management. I have seen firsthand how antimicrobial resistance (#AMR) can complicate treatment, making recovery slower and more uncertain. 

This issue affects everyone, not just those with existing health conditions. Taking simple steps, such as practising good hand hygiene and using antibiotics responsibly, can help reduce the spread of resistant infections. 

Preserving the effectiveness of antibiotics is essential to ensuring that they remain a reliable treatment option in the future. Without urgent action, more people will face infections that are increasingly difficult to treat, putting lives and medical progress at risk.” 

Gavin is 26 years old and from Malta. His testimony is part of the #Stories_of_AMR campaign – a collection of first-person accounts from across Europe and Central Asia showing us once again why #AntimicrobialResistance is a topic that concerns each and every one of us. 

🔗 Link in bio to find out more.

👏 Great news, our hands-on training is now officially accredited by VetCEE! 

This means that our hands-on training counts as Continuing Veterinary Education (CVE), a requirement in many European countries to maintain your veterinary licence.

VetCEE is an international non-profit organisation that guarantees high quality, cross-border recognised CPD for veterinarians across Europe. 

🧑‍⚕️ Important: this accreditation is only valid for veterinarians attending in person.

Imagine strolling through a park when a lion suddenly appears on the path ahead. In that instant, your brain automatically activates the fight-or-flight response, preparing you to either stand your ground or make a swift escape – the latter being the usual course of action.

The fight-or-flight response is one way people cope with perceived danger. It speeds up the heart rate, suppresses the immune system and increases blood glucose and blood pressure, priming for action.

For years, researchers have examined the physiological effects of perceiving potential harm, but the assumption has been that the fight-or-flight response has different effects on the brain.

Recent research challenges this by showing how the brain undergoes its own major metabolic upheaval to prepare for fighting or fleeing.

The findings uncover molecular biological defence mechanisms that could potentially be harnessed to develop new medicines for conditions such as epilepsy or insomnia.

“The same mechanisms that drive the fight-or-flight response also wake us up each morning. More deeply understanding how the brain regulates this process could thus lead to more effective insomnia medicines. However, this requires more advanced techniques for studying this phenomenon in living animals,” explains a researcher behind the study, Maiken Nedergaard, Professor, Center for Translational Neuromedicine, University of Copenhagen, Denmark and Center for Translational Neuromedicine, University of Rochester, NY, USA.

【当事者の声】眼科疾患と薬剤耐性の経験（2025年6月10日）
[Lived Experiences] Experiences with Eye Disease and AMR (June 10, 2025)

AMRアライアンス・ジャパン（事務局：日本医療政策機構）では、薬剤耐性対策の政策推進に向けて、国内外の薬剤耐性（AMR: Antimicrobial Resistance）の患者・当事者と共に活動してきました。活動の一環として、2021年からAMR対策に関わる市民の声を集めています。

今回は、継続的に眼科治療を受けている丸山純一氏より、長期間に及ぶ抗菌薬使用が薬剤耐性を誘導した結果、将来の治療選択肢に影響を与える可能性について語っていただきました。特に現在、唯一視野が保たれている左眼の白内障手術に対する不安と、薬剤耐性という課題の身近さについて共有いただきました。

Aiming to advance policies to combat antimicrobial resistance (AMR), AMR Alliance Japan (Secretariat: Health and Global Policy Institute (HGPI)) has been engaged in joint action with people impacted by AMR and those close to them in Japan and abroad. As part of these activities, starting in 2021, AMR Alliance Japan has been gathering the voices of citizens who have been involved in AMR control.

This installment focuses on Mr. Junichi Maruyama’s experiences with continuous ophthalmologic treatment and AMR. Mr. Maruyama’s current source of concern is having cataract surgery for his left eye, which is his only remaining source of vision. He highlighted how long-term antimicrobial use that results in AMR can impact one’s future treatment options and shared how AMR is an issue that is close at hand in his life.
